A pie chart is a circular graph to view data

Use the pie ( ) function to draw pie charts

Bitmap(file=“out.png”)
X <- c(10,20,40)
Pie(x)

Note: the size of each pie is determined by comparing the value with all the other values, by using
this formula

The value divided by the sum and all values: x/sum(x)

Start angle
You can change the start angle of the pie chart with the init.angle parameter
The value of init.angle is defined with angle in degrees, where default angle is 0

x <- c(10,20,30,50)
Pie(x, init.angle = 90)

Labels and header

Use the label parameter to add a label to the pie chart, and use the main parameter to add a header

X <- c(10,20,30,50)

Mylabel <- c(“Apple”, “Banana”, “Cherries”, “Dates”)

Pie(x, label = mylabel, main = “Fruits”)

Legend

To add a list of explanation for each pie, use the legend( ) function :

Bitmap(file=“out.png”)
X<- c(vectors)

Legend ( “bottomright”, mylabel, fill = colors )

It creates a table/legend with the objects/vectors with their label/name and the color dynamic
